1
00:00:00,270 --> 00:00:01,570
Kang Jun Ho!

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:04,280
Jang Mi! Kang Jun Ho!

3
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:06,240
- Kang Jun Ho!
- I said, let me out!

4
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:08,180
- Kang Jun Ho!
- Open the door! I said, open it!

5
00:00:09,510 --> 00:00:13,020
Kang Jun Ho! Jang Mi! Kang Jun Ho!

6
00:00:13,320 --> 00:00:14,350
Kang Jun Ho!

7
00:00:15,190 --> 00:00:16,190
Darn it!

8
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:17,960
Darn it!

9
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:33,540
So, are you still drunk?

10
00:00:33,810 --> 00:00:35,010
Of course not.

11
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:38,910
Anyway, I'm sorry, Chairman.

12
00:00:39,180 --> 00:00:43,550
I'm sorry I couldn't hold my liquor
and made a scene.

13
00:00:43,820 --> 00:00:46,550
But who was that girl?

14
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:50,720
Who is she to be having such a private,
heartfelt reunion with you?

15
00:00:50,790 --> 00:00:53,490
And holding hands and crying,
just the two of you.

16
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:55,290
Act your age.

17
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:56,930
Just act your age!

18
00:00:58,160 --> 00:00:59,160
Gosh!

19
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,430
Wait, honey.

20
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:05,440
How can you just run off to your study
without answering me?

21
00:01:06,570 --> 00:01:08,570
Are you sure she's Father's old flame?

22
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:11,840
- I'm telling you she is.
- Then why did you ask who she was?

23
00:01:12,540 --> 00:01:13,750
You don't know either, do you?

24
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:17,020
His first love, maybe?

25
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:19,480
That might be it.

26
00:01:19,780 --> 00:01:23,790
- What does she look like? Is she pretty?
- Not prettier than me, of course.

27
00:01:25,060 --> 00:01:27,490
But she did look classy.

28
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:30,600
Was her name Seong Hye?

29
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:33,500
Right, he said something like Seong Hye.

30
00:01:34,070 --> 00:01:35,070
Seong Hye?

31
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,580
Her name is Seong Hye?

32
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,880
Seong Sil, Seong Hye.

33
00:01:49,750 --> 00:01:52,080
Chairman Ma's wife was Lee Seong Sil.

34
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:55,990
Then Seong Hye must be her older
or younger sister.

35
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,400
Manager Lee.

36
00:02:05,900 --> 00:02:08,470
Chairman Ma's wife's name was
Lee Seong Sil, right?

37
00:02:09,470 --> 00:02:11,470
Look into Lee Seong Sil's
family background.

38
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:15,370
See if she has a younger
or older sister named Seong Hye.

39
00:02:15,970 --> 00:02:17,010
Yes, ma'am. I'll get right on it.

40
00:02:18,140 --> 00:02:21,650
For the sandwich, I'll have rye bread,
and could you toast it lightly inside?

41
00:02:22,210 --> 00:02:26,680
And no pickles or jalapenos,
but with extra olives.

42
00:02:27,650 --> 00:02:29,320
I have some peculiar tastes myself...

43
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:31,220
I can't believe someone else
orders the same thing.

44
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:34,230
- How about that.
- Will there be anything else?

45
00:02:35,390 --> 00:02:38,400
For the sauce, just a thin line
of mayonnaise, please.

46
00:02:38,860 --> 00:02:43,170
And a hot Americano
with two ice cubes in it.

47
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:45,040
So it's the perfect temperature
to drink right away.

48
00:02:47,670 --> 00:02:48,670
Thanks.

49
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:50,780
Are you ready to order, sir?

50
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:52,840
Yes.

51
00:02:54,980 --> 00:02:57,050
I'll have the exact same thing
she just ordered.

52
00:02:58,250 --> 00:03:00,150
If he sees that our tastes
are identical...

53
00:03:00,450 --> 00:03:01,990
he's bound to be interested.

54
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:05,690
Please, just walk over to me,
Manager Lee. Come on.

55
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:07,160
Come on, come on.

56
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:20,270
Hello, Lawyer Han.

57
00:03:22,170 --> 00:03:24,180
Hello.

58
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,180
What brings you here?

59
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:29,450
This is my regular spot.

60
00:03:30,350 --> 00:03:34,120
- What about you, Lawyer Han?
- I come here often, too.

61
00:03:34,990 --> 00:03:37,390
What a coincidence that
we have the same regular spot.

62
00:03:39,390 --> 00:03:42,130
That's right.
I've been meaning to return your suit.

63
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:44,100
I wasn't sure how to reach you.

64
00:03:44,730 --> 00:03:46,430
I thought about asking Jun Ho for it...

65
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:48,400
but I figured that might be
a little awkward to explain.

66
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,000
I see.

67
00:03:50,940 --> 00:03:52,940
You really didn't have to worry about it.

68
00:03:54,210 --> 00:03:58,240
Orders 234 and 235. Your orders are ready.

69
00:03:58,740 --> 00:04:00,950
- One second.
- My order is ready too,

70
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:02,310
so I'll get it for you.

71
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:09,620
Yes! I'm halfway there.

72
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,360
What do you know.

73
00:04:15,490 --> 00:04:18,160
So she's not even bothering
to cook at all anymore, is she?

74
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,570
This is pathetic.
Fine, I'll make myself ramyeon.

75
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:22,670
With an egg...

76
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:24,340
Oh my.

77
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:26,140
There's no ramyeon either.

78
00:04:27,410 --> 00:04:28,840
And no eggs in the fridge.

79
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:32,280
Gosh, there's nothing to eat
in this lousy house.

80
00:04:32,910 --> 00:04:34,610
Gosh, I'm starving to death.

81
00:04:41,390 --> 00:04:42,390
Cheers.

82
00:04:45,620 --> 00:04:48,290
Manager Lee.
Am I making you uncomfortable?

83
00:04:48,590 --> 00:04:49,590
Pardon?

84
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:52,560
No, that is not it.

85
00:04:52,630 --> 00:04:56,000
CEO Chae may be my sworn enemy,

86
00:04:56,670 --> 00:04:59,040
but I have nothing against you.

87
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:02,840
You're just doing your job
as CEO Chae's assistant.

88
00:05:04,710 --> 00:05:06,040
I'm not uncomfortable either.

89
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:09,310
By the way.

90
00:05:09,650 --> 00:05:12,380
Can I get your contact info?
I need to return your suit.

91
00:05:12,550 --> 00:05:14,550
No. Please don't trouble yourself.

92
00:05:14,850 --> 00:05:17,320
When you stop by the hotel to see
Kang Jun Ho or Lawyer Kang,

93
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:19,320
you can just leave it at the front desk.

94
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:21,760
All right, then.

95
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:23,560
Then,

96
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:25,200
I'll be on my way.

97
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:28,300
Yes.

98
00:05:38,410 --> 00:05:40,310
He seems like such a decent guy,

99
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:43,150
so why is he by that witch's side?

100
00:05:43,820 --> 00:05:44,820
What a waste.

101
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:50,720
I think we should trace the route
Kang Jun Ho's car took from the church.

102
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:53,760
Yes, I'd appreciate that.

103
00:05:54,430 --> 00:05:58,600
Detective, I'm asking this
as a personal favor, so...

104
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:02,330
You mean, keep it off the record.
I get it, so just drop it.

105
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:04,600
I'm letting it slide
just this once, Lawyer Kang.

106
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:07,770
Thank you. There are some circumstances.

107
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:12,010
My brother suddenly took off,
and I need to find him right away.

108
00:06:12,710 --> 00:06:14,080
Anyway, thank you.

109
00:06:15,380 --> 00:06:17,680
Seriously, what is that bastard
planning to do with our Jang Mi?

110
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,150
Why did he take her
and even throw her phone away?

111
00:06:19,650 --> 00:06:20,990
This is infuriating! Seriously!

112
00:06:21,250 --> 00:06:24,460
This is Jang Mi's. It's Jang Mi's phone.

113
00:06:25,690 --> 00:06:29,190
Baek Ho, what are you going to do?
She was taken right after the ceremony.

114
00:06:30,660 --> 00:06:32,660
Baek Ho's arm hurts.

115
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:34,300
Shouldn't you go to the hospital?

116
00:06:34,670 --> 00:06:37,640
I'm fine. Finding Jang Mi is
the only thing that matters right now.

117
00:06:38,370 --> 00:06:40,540
Jang Mi's gone. Where is she?

118
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:44,780
- Our Jang Mi is gone! Our Jang Mi!
- Mom, she'll be okay.

119
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:46,810
Nothing will happen to Jang Mi.

120
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:49,380
I wonder why the Chairman is calling.

121
00:06:50,010 --> 00:06:51,020
Jang Mi...

122
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:52,580
Yes, Chairman.

123
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:57,220
You can't get in touch with Jang Mi?

124
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:01,130
I'll come explain everything
in person right away.

125
00:07:02,530 --> 00:07:06,130
What was that again?
Kang Jun Ho took my Jang Mi?

126
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:08,930
- Where to?
- I'm not sure yet.

127
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:12,140
Jang Mi and I were having a private
commitment ceremony at the church...

128
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:16,240
So Kang Jun Ho was so shocked
that he took my Jang Mi?

129
00:07:17,140 --> 00:07:19,140
Yes. I'm so sorry.

130
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:21,180
That insolent brat!

131
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:24,420
So that's why I couldn't reach her.

132
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:27,150
Yes, sir. I'll be sure to find her
before the night is over.

133
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:29,690
Okay. Do you have any idea
where he might've taken her?

134
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:32,190
No, not yet.

135
00:07:32,460 --> 00:07:33,860
For crying out loud!

136
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:38,360
That bastard.
How dare he kidnap my granddaughter?

137
00:07:38,430 --> 00:07:41,970
I will do whatever it takes to find her,
so please don't worry too much, Chairman.

138
00:07:45,970 --> 00:07:47,570
Hong Ju! Something terrible has happened!

139
00:07:48,210 --> 00:07:51,810
- What?
- Apparently, Kang Jun Ho took Jang Mi.

140
00:07:52,710 --> 00:07:55,880
- I know.
- What do you mean? How do you know?

141
00:07:58,550 --> 00:08:00,620
Jin Hong Ju. How do you know?

142
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,290
Spit it out, now!

143
00:08:03,820 --> 00:08:06,090
We have to know what happened
so we can respond!

144
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:09,560
She's right. We have to stop Kang Jun Ho
before he ruins everything.

145
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:12,460
Jang Mi has to end up with Baek Ho.

146
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:13,760
Talk!

147
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:17,370
He found out that Baek Ho and Oh Jang Mi
were having a commitment ceremony.

148
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,840
I think Jun Ho just snapped.

149
00:08:20,740 --> 00:08:23,410
It was you, wasn't it?
You put my Jun Ho up to this, right?

150
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:25,580
That's not true.

151
00:08:26,210 --> 00:08:29,210
Besides, Jun Ho is not someone
you can just egg on.

152
00:08:36,420 --> 00:08:38,890
Where on earth could he be?
Where did he go?

153
00:08:39,490 --> 00:08:40,490
Kang Jun Ho,

154
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:44,060
so you're willing to throw away Dream
and everything just for Oh Jang Mi?

155
00:08:44,660 --> 00:08:46,300
You foolish, foolish boy.

156
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:50,300
Why is he being so reckless?

157
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,770
- Let me take a look.
- I'm fine.

158
00:09:21,830 --> 00:09:23,970
What do you mean you're fine?
Your foot hurts.

159
00:09:24,070 --> 00:09:25,270
Icing it should help.

160
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:26,670
I said I'm fine!

161
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:29,540
See? It hurts, doesn't it?

162
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:31,840
Then why did you try to run away?

163
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:34,480
You were bound to twist your ankle
running in those shoes.

164
00:09:34,710 --> 00:09:35,910
So you're happy about that, aren't you?

165
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,280
That I can't run away
because my foot hurts.

166
00:09:38,550 --> 00:09:41,220
The old lady here lives alone,
so it's not like I can borrow a phone.

167
00:09:41,450 --> 00:09:42,690
This must be just perfect for you.

168
00:09:44,090 --> 00:09:46,960
Wait a minute.
Did you scout this place out beforehand?

169
00:09:48,190 --> 00:09:51,100
Were you waiting for the perfect chance
to drag me here?

170
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,360
Of course not.

171
00:09:52,930 --> 00:09:54,470
Don't be so angry, Jang Mi.

172
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:58,040
Don't you realize the more you do this,
the further you push me away?

173
00:09:58,300 --> 00:10:00,200
When did you ever feel anything for me?

174
00:10:00,670 --> 00:10:03,310
Jang Mi, have you ever once given me
any serious thought?

175
00:10:04,010 --> 00:10:07,380
You've never even tried to understand
who I am as a person.

176
00:10:07,610 --> 00:10:09,250
So is this your idea of revenge?

177
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:12,550
That's not what this is about. Revenge?

178
00:10:12,950 --> 00:10:15,490
- Don't dismiss my love for you.
- If you really loved someone,

179
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:18,590
you wouldn't tear their heart
to shreds like this.

180
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:20,730
What you're doing right now...

181
00:10:21,590 --> 00:10:23,690
How is it any different from
when Chae Hwa Young kidnapped my mother...

182
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:26,730
- and locked her away?
- I didn't kidnap you, Jang Mi.

183
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,530
I came to claim my bride from Baek Ho.

184
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,170
You were always meant to be my bride.

185
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:36,870
Do you really think this is a kidnapping?
Jang Mi, is that what you really think?

186
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:41,210
I just want you to hear me out,

187
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:45,520
and see how much I love you.
I'm trying to keep you away from Baek Ho.

188
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:46,920
Unbelievable.

189
00:10:47,620 --> 00:10:48,790
There's just no talking to you.

190
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:51,890
Fine.

191
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:56,060
Then what is it you want from me?

192
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:59,400
- Jang Mi.
- Actually, come to think of it,

193
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,530
I might have been too harsh on you.

194
00:11:03,730 --> 00:11:07,100
You're a much better person
than Chae Hwa Young.

195
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:09,170
That's right.

196
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:12,310
There was a time I truly admired
and respected you.

197
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:16,750
From overcoming that terrible leukemia
to becoming a chef,

198
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:20,650
I knew all about the hardships
and adversity you endured.

199
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:24,560
Your diligence, your fighting spirit.

200
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:28,130
You were a shining light in my youth.

201
00:11:29,090 --> 00:11:30,260
And the person I idolized...

202
00:11:30,930 --> 00:11:32,330
was you, Chef Kang Jun Ho.

203
00:11:34,330 --> 00:11:36,200
But the person who once
shone so brightly...

204
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:38,670
How did you turn into this monster?

205
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:42,140
Why are you dragging yourself into
the gutter with Chae Hwa Young? Why?

206
00:11:47,210 --> 00:11:48,210
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

207
00:11:48,210 --> 00:11:49,310
Nowhere.

208
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,920
I can't think of anywhere else
Jun Ho would be.

209
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:54,790
Jun Ho is a rational person.
He won't do anything reckless.

210
00:11:54,850 --> 00:11:56,990
A rational person kidnaps Oh Jang Mi
and runs off with her?

211
00:11:57,620 --> 00:11:59,720
Of all the ways to ruin everything
at the last minute.

212
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:01,630
I'm so incredibly frustrated.

213
00:12:02,330 --> 00:12:04,800
I'm sure he'll come back safely.

214
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:06,800
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

215
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,540
Gosh, who's calling now?

216
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:22,750
- Nam Bong, it's me.
- Hwa Young. How have you been?

217
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:26,920
What? Jun Ho...

218
00:12:27,690 --> 00:12:29,420
kidnapped Oh Jang Mi?

219
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,860
Can you think of any place
he might have gone?

220
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:38,300
I called hoping you might have some idea
where he could be.

221
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:39,530
Well...

222
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:41,500
Chae Hwa Young.

223
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,770
It figures your son would pull a stunt
just like you.

224
00:12:44,170 --> 00:12:46,940
Give me that!
I need to find out what happened.

225
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:50,840
Hello? What's going on?
What do you mean, he kidnapped her?

226
00:12:51,010 --> 00:12:55,480
It seems he showed up and took Jang Mi
at her ceremony with Lawyer Kang.

227
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:58,380
So you have no idea
where he could be either, right?

228
00:13:00,450 --> 00:13:01,450
All right, then.

229
00:13:02,050 --> 00:13:04,050
Hwa Young, wait!

230
00:13:05,420 --> 00:13:06,460
She hung up.

231
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:09,790
You seem pretty broken up about that.

232
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:15,500
Han Young Ja. I mean, Young Ja.
Let's try to be a little civilized.

233
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:18,340
What do you think you're doing,
snatching the phone while I'm on a call?

234
00:13:18,470 --> 00:13:23,110
Kang Nam Bong. Or should I say, Nam Bong.
Why don't you get a grip?

235
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:26,610
How can you be so shameless,
still calling out for Hwa Young now?

236
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:29,180
Do you have any idea what's going on?

237
00:13:29,610 --> 00:13:33,650
Jun Ho kidnapped Jang Mi,
who was about to marry Baek Ho.

238
00:13:34,590 --> 00:13:36,350
Where in the world could he be?

239
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:39,920
And our poor Baek Ho.
He must be absolutely heartbroken.

240
00:13:40,390 --> 00:13:41,460
This is so upsetting.

241
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:42,960
Detective, what's the update?

242
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,360
What did you say?

243
00:13:45,630 --> 00:13:47,930
You found Kang Jun Ho's car
under an underpass?

244
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:51,570
- Where is that? I'm on my way.
- Does that mean they found Jang Mi?

245
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:55,670
There's no point in coming.
It looks like he switched cars there.

246
00:13:55,740 --> 00:13:56,740
What?

247
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:58,440
What do you mean?

248
00:13:58,510 --> 00:14:02,480
It seems he anticipated being tracked
and switched cars.

249
00:14:02,810 --> 00:14:06,120
- There are no CCTVs by the underpass.
- Then...

250
00:14:06,580 --> 00:14:08,920
Does that mean there's no way
to find Jang Mi?

251
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:25,800
Thank you.

252
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:34,480
Jang Mi.

253
00:14:35,210 --> 00:14:39,350
- Here, eat up. You must be hungry.
- I don't have an appetite. You eat.

254
00:14:43,420 --> 00:14:44,420
A long time ago...

255
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:47,560
I was adopted once.

256
00:14:48,690 --> 00:14:49,860
My adoptive parents...

257
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:52,260
had never raised a child before,

258
00:14:53,460 --> 00:14:55,230
so I don't know if they thought
kids don't eat much or what,

259
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:57,470
but I was always hungry.

260
00:14:58,340 --> 00:15:01,170
But there was a villa
near my adoptive home,

261
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:03,810
and there was a beautiful lady
who stayed there.

262
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:08,080
Whenever I visited,
she always made sure I had a warm meal.

263
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:10,550
She used to tell me,

264
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:13,050
to never, ever go hungry.

265
00:15:13,850 --> 00:15:15,590
She said you need food in your belly...

266
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:18,190
to have the strength to face the world.

267
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:20,620
When I see you, Jang Mi,

268
00:15:21,130 --> 00:15:22,930
I'm sometimes reminded of that woman.

269
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:27,730
If she taught me about the warmth
of a good meal,

270
00:15:28,830 --> 00:15:30,030
then you, Jang Mi,

271
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:32,940
are the person who taught me
about the warmth of human kindness.

272
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,740
So before you were adopted by Lawyer Han,

273
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:39,410
you were adopted by another family first?

274
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:41,050
Yes.

275
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,810
The moment I was diagnosed with leukemia,

276
00:15:44,580 --> 00:15:46,020
they immediately sent me back.

277
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:50,320
I guess there was no reason
to raise a child who was going to die.

278
00:15:51,420 --> 00:15:52,960
The hospital bills
would have been high, too.

279
00:15:54,190 --> 00:15:57,130
That woman also taught me
how to read and write.

280
00:15:57,760 --> 00:15:59,330
Back then, I didn't even know
what my own mother looked like,

281
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:03,770
I used to think that if I had a mother,
I'd want her to be just like that woman.

282
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:05,800
So, being just a kid,

283
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:08,440
I had this pearl hairpin
that I always carried with me,

284
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:11,710
and one time, I brought it along
because I wanted to give it to her.

285
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:15,710
The pearl hairpin
you always carried with you?

286
00:16:16,780 --> 00:16:19,550
You mean you carried that with you
all the time?

287
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:24,390
Yes. I think Chae Hwa Young
gave it to me when she abandoned me.

288
00:16:25,260 --> 00:16:26,820
Even when I was moved
between foster homes,

289
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,630
it was always there among my things.

290
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:31,030
Chae Hwa Young?

291
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:37,270
Who is this child?

292
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:40,670
Why was Chae Hwa Young
crying over this photo?

293
00:16:43,310 --> 00:16:45,710
This is my mom's hairpin.

294
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:50,910
Wait, was that villa in Taean,
by any chance?

295
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,780
- Yes.
- Then it's possible...

296
00:16:55,090 --> 00:16:58,660
that you and my mom might have met before.

297
00:16:59,460 --> 00:17:00,620
What are you talking about?

298
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:04,360
Wait.

299
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:07,230
Are you saying the woman
I met at the villa...

300
00:17:08,230 --> 00:17:09,930
was your mother?

301
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,540
It's possible.

302
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:15,640
Chae Hwa Young stole that hairpin
from my house.

303
00:17:29,820 --> 00:17:31,360
Still no word?

304
00:17:32,860 --> 00:17:35,530
The sun's about to come up.
How can this be happening?

305
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:37,800
Kang Jun Ho. I could kill him.

306
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,830
It'll be okay, Baek Ho.

307
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:41,800
I can't just wait around.

308
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:46,340
I don't care how late it is.
I'm calling her to ask what she knows.

309
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:52,110
Yes, ma'am.

310
00:17:52,580 --> 00:17:54,210
Sorry to call so late, Team Leader Jin.

311
00:17:54,550 --> 00:17:58,380
But have you heard anything from him yet?

312
00:17:59,580 --> 00:18:01,720
- No.
- We're in big trouble.

313
00:18:02,150 --> 00:18:05,460
At this rate, my Jun Ho is going
to face legal charges.

314
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:09,390
What? Wait. You mean Jun Ho?

315
00:18:09,690 --> 00:18:12,860
If he's branded a kidnapper,
Jun Ho's life is over!

316
00:18:12,860 --> 00:18:14,060
What am I going to do?

317
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:16,070
Let me.

318
00:18:16,570 --> 00:18:19,670
Team Leader Jin, if you know anything,
you need to tell me about my brother.

319
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:21,370
We're running out of time.

320
00:18:23,070 --> 00:18:24,070
I mean...

321
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:26,680
You know something, don't you,
Team Leader Jin?

322
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:31,550
The truth is
I'm the one who lent Jun Ho my car.

323
00:18:32,180 --> 00:18:36,650
- What?
- He swapped cars there.

324
00:18:36,850 --> 00:18:38,720
But I don't know where he went either.

325
00:18:39,190 --> 00:18:40,620
Does the car have GPS tracking?

326
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:41,960
Yes.

327
00:18:42,660 --> 00:18:44,060
I'm sorry, Baek Ho.

328
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:47,600
But I could not stand the idea
of you marrying Oh Jang Mi, so...

329
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:48,700
What's the license plate number?

330
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:50,330
Just tell me the number. Now!

331
00:19:09,220 --> 00:19:10,220
What are you doing?

332
00:19:10,490 --> 00:19:11,590
It's nothing.

333
00:19:12,260 --> 00:19:13,390
You looked cold.

334
00:19:13,690 --> 00:19:15,260
Stay at least one meter away from me.

335
00:19:16,330 --> 00:19:18,500
Nothing's going to happen. Don't worry.

336
00:19:18,830 --> 00:19:21,100
I can't take you home now
because it's too late,

337
00:19:21,770 --> 00:19:23,930
but I'll take you home
first thing in the morning.

338
00:19:24,370 --> 00:19:26,940
So just relax and get some sleep.
Your feet must be sore.

339
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:41,550
Don't sleep huddled over there.

340
00:19:42,290 --> 00:19:43,490
You can sleep comfortably over here.

341
00:19:46,090 --> 00:19:48,460
No. I'm fine.

342
00:19:48,930 --> 00:19:51,330
You sleep here. Don't worry about me.

343
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:54,900
You're being so stubborn.

344
00:19:55,830 --> 00:19:57,100
Come on, come over here and sleep.

345
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:58,600
What do you think you're doing?

346
00:19:58,670 --> 00:20:01,670
Relax, I'm not going to try anything.
I told you nothing would happen.

347
00:20:01,740 --> 00:20:03,670
Stay at least one meter away from me.

348
00:20:03,970 --> 00:20:06,580
Fine. You sleep here comfortably.

349
00:20:07,010 --> 00:20:09,050
I'll just huddle over there
and get some sleep.

350
00:20:23,590 --> 00:20:24,630
Baek Ho.

351
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,060
You must be so worried about me.

352
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:29,530
Just wait a little longer.

353
00:20:43,950 --> 00:20:46,220
Hey. Why are you sleeping here?

354
00:20:49,090 --> 00:20:50,490
I was sleeping over in the corner,

355
00:20:51,390 --> 00:20:53,660
but I must have gotten cold
and crawled in here in my sleep.

356
00:20:55,430 --> 00:20:56,430
Did you sleep well?

357
00:20:57,630 --> 00:21:00,660
Waking up to your face in the morning
makes me so happy.

358
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:03,700
Now I see why people get married.

359
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:07,670
Stop talking nonsense
and just get ready to go.

360
00:21:11,610 --> 00:21:12,610
Baek Ho!

361
00:21:13,610 --> 00:21:15,380
Kang Jun Ho, are you out of your mind?

362
00:21:16,310 --> 00:21:19,480
Hey! How could you do this?

363
00:21:20,620 --> 00:21:23,250
Baek Ho, it's not what you think.
Nothing happened.

364
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:25,820
Hey, Baek Ho, stop it! You punk!

365
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:29,730
You've got nerve. What were you thinking,
running off with our Jang Mi?

366
00:21:29,860 --> 00:21:32,960
- Do you know how worried we were?
- Tae Pyung, stop.

367
00:21:33,030 --> 00:21:35,700
Oh Tae Pyung, take Jang Mi
and wait in the car.

368
00:21:35,870 --> 00:21:36,900
Now!

369
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:44,740
You're a cruel bastard.

370
00:21:45,780 --> 00:21:47,110
There's no excuse for this.

371
00:21:47,510 --> 00:21:49,750
We grew up under the same roof
for over 30 years.

372
00:21:50,210 --> 00:21:51,720
How could you run away
with the woman I love?

373
00:21:51,780 --> 00:21:54,380
Have you forgotten?
I'm Chae Hwa Young's son.

374
00:21:54,650 --> 00:21:57,020
- Which means I'm capable of anything.
- What did you say?

375
00:21:59,060 --> 00:22:00,220
And just so you know,

376
00:22:01,220 --> 00:22:03,630
you won't believe this,
but as for Jang Mi's feelings,

377
00:22:04,390 --> 00:22:06,630
after spending the night together,
she's starting to fall for me.

378
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:09,370
And you'll see the proof soon enough.

379
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:11,400
Say that again.

380
00:22:11,570 --> 00:22:15,240
- You saw us. Sleeping together.
- Shut up!

381
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:18,640
You think I'd believe that crap?

382
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:20,940
If you say it one more time...

383
00:22:21,550 --> 00:22:23,680
If you say that filthy lie one more time,

384
00:22:24,180 --> 00:22:25,980
I won't hold back. You got that?

385
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:37,630
As of today, the brother I loved
and was so proud of...

386
00:22:38,260 --> 00:22:39,730
my brother, Kang Jun Ho, is dead to me.

387
00:22:40,330 --> 00:22:41,470
I don't have a brother anymore.

388
00:22:42,770 --> 00:22:45,900
From now on, you're my enemy,
and I'm coming for you.

389
00:22:46,470 --> 00:22:48,970
The pain and betrayal I felt today.

390
00:22:49,710 --> 00:22:51,240
I'm going to give it right back to you,
Kang Jun Ho.

391
00:22:55,810 --> 00:22:56,810
Fine!

392
00:22:58,010 --> 00:23:00,250
I've been alone since the day
I was born anyway.

393
00:23:00,980 --> 00:23:02,090
A little brother like you?

394
00:23:02,950 --> 00:23:03,950
Family?

395
00:23:07,220 --> 00:23:08,360
I don't need any of it.

396
00:23:27,540 --> 00:23:28,550
Baek Ho.

397
00:23:36,350 --> 00:23:39,320
Let's go. Are you hurt anywhere?

398
00:23:39,690 --> 00:23:42,830
I twisted my ankle trying to get away.

399
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:48,500
Get on my back. I'll carry you to the car.

400
00:23:52,870 --> 00:23:54,140
You've been through a lot,
haven't you, Jang Mi?

401
00:24:01,340 --> 00:24:02,350
Come on.

402
00:24:03,780 --> 00:24:05,820
I'm warning you, I'm heavy.

403
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:15,690
I'm sorry, Jang Mi.

404
00:24:17,190 --> 00:24:18,660
Even though I know you so well...

405
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,870
for a second, I doubted you.

406
00:24:22,770 --> 00:24:24,700
Under the circumstances,
I can't blame you.

407
00:24:25,570 --> 00:24:27,270
But the police might be on their way.

408
00:24:27,940 --> 00:24:29,970
I had no choice. It was the only way
I could find you.

409
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,740
I don't want to press charges
against Jun Ho.

410
00:24:34,110 --> 00:24:38,250
Can we just tell them
I came with him willingly?

411
00:24:39,680 --> 00:24:41,120
You should call your mother first.

412
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:42,950
She must be worried sick.

413
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:44,590
Okay, I will.

414
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:00,640
About Jun Ho...

415
00:25:01,340 --> 00:25:04,510
What a relief that it all blew over
without the police getting involved.

416
00:25:05,710 --> 00:25:08,580
I wonder how Jang Mi wrapped Chairman Ma
around her finger.

417
00:25:08,710 --> 00:25:10,480
It would cause a huge scandal
for the company,

418
00:25:10,810 --> 00:25:13,320
so he probably buried the issue
before it escalated.

419
00:25:13,980 --> 00:25:17,720
Still, this has put him even further
out of favor with Chairman Ma.

420
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:23,730
Lee Seong Sil's younger sister
is indeed Lee Seong Hye.

421
00:25:24,130 --> 00:25:25,700
Apparently, she's been living in America
this whole time.

422
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,600
- Really?
- Yes.

423
00:25:28,130 --> 00:25:31,430
- Secretary Kim's been acting strange.
- Strange how?

424
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:34,500
I heard he's looking for people
who worked at Chairman Ma's house...

425
00:25:34,570 --> 00:25:35,970
about 50 years ago.

426
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:40,940
Fifty years ago? That's around the time
Chairman Ma's daughter died.

427
00:25:41,010 --> 00:25:43,980
And Dong Seok would've been there
around that time, too.

428
00:25:47,180 --> 00:25:50,750
It really seems like Chairman Ma
is desperately hiding something.

429
00:25:50,950 --> 00:25:54,290
Right. And on top of that, it seems
Seong Hye is looking for someone, too.

430
00:25:55,230 --> 00:25:56,230
Is she?

431
00:25:57,160 --> 00:25:58,160
But why?

432
00:26:00,460 --> 00:26:01,670
I have a bad feeling about this.

433
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:06,940
A DNA registry, you say?

434
00:26:07,370 --> 00:26:09,040
You never know.

435
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:12,210
Eun Hye might have registered,
trying to find her parents.

436
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:15,650
You just have to go to the police station
and register.

437
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:19,480
And some people found relatives
that way through DNA matches.

438
00:26:19,680 --> 00:26:21,820
We have to do it right away, then.

439
00:26:21,950 --> 00:26:24,720
Whatever it takes,
we have to find our Eun Hye.

440
00:26:27,390 --> 00:26:30,160
Let's get dinner together sometime.

441
00:26:30,930 --> 00:26:31,930
Okay, sounds good.

442
00:26:32,130 --> 00:26:35,770
You're leaving soon,
so you should come by more often.

443
00:26:35,970 --> 00:26:39,140
- Okay. Get home safe.
- Okay.

444
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:42,370
Hey, Chief Oh, it's me.

445
00:26:44,670 --> 00:26:46,780
Wait. Hold on.

446
00:26:47,480 --> 00:26:50,680
You may have waltzed in here,
but you can't just waltz out.

447
00:26:50,780 --> 00:26:53,420
- Mom, stop it.
- Stop what?

448
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:56,750
Who does this woman think she is,
trying to move in on my territory?

449
00:26:57,690 --> 00:27:01,960
I'm the Chairman's...
No, no. I'm his mistress.

450
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:05,730
No, that's not it.
Anyway, don't you know who I am to him?

451
00:27:06,960 --> 00:27:08,300
I can't say I do.

452
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:13,570
So you want to play it that way?

453
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:18,910
What are you trying to leech off him,
coming here all the time?

454
00:27:19,110 --> 00:27:20,710
How dare you be so rude?

455
00:27:22,350 --> 00:27:26,580
You clearly don't know who I am.
I'm the Chairman's sister-in-law.

456
00:27:28,280 --> 00:27:30,020
Sister-in-law, my foot.

457
00:27:30,250 --> 00:27:34,520
That's how it always starts,
with all the cutesy family names...

458
00:27:34,590 --> 00:27:35,960
and before you know it,
it's "honey" and "darling!"

459
00:27:37,260 --> 00:27:38,500
Spit it out.

460
00:27:38,930 --> 00:27:41,970
Why are you really here,
pretending to be his sister-in-law?

461
00:27:42,030 --> 00:27:43,200
I can't believe this woman.

462
00:27:43,770 --> 00:27:48,300
I am Lee Seong Hye, younger sister
of his first wife, Lee Seong Sil.

463
00:27:49,070 --> 00:27:52,840
I'm here because I heard
my late sister's daughter is alive.

464
00:27:53,180 --> 00:27:54,210
Now, get out of my way.

465
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:56,780
The Chairman's daughter is alive?

466
00:28:22,810 --> 00:28:24,240
(The First Man)

467
00:28:24,310 --> 00:28:27,040
She was called "the necklace baby,"
until the director gave her a surname...

468
00:28:27,040 --> 00:28:28,550
and named her Park Young Mi.

469
00:28:28,750 --> 00:28:31,180
Then shouldn't it be easy to find her?

470
00:28:31,550 --> 00:28:34,980
You stole everything from me!
My name, my place...

471
00:28:35,190 --> 00:28:37,990
and even Jun Ho.
No one is even looking for me.

472
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:39,960
Where does that leave me?

473
00:28:40,290 --> 00:28:43,790
What is wrong with you?
Why did you have Han Young Ja bring this?

474
00:28:44,230 --> 00:28:46,760
Don't tell me you're trying to betray me.

475
00:28:48,330 --> 00:28:50,330
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
